  "entity_type": "vehicle",
  "overview": {
    "value": "Zhuque-2 is a Chinese medium-class orbital launch vehicle developed by LandSpace, powered by liquid oxygen and methane, and was the first methane-fueled rocket to reach orbit, on its second flight on 12 July 2023. The baseline Zhuque-2 can lift 4,000 kg to a 200 km LEO and 1,500 kg to a 500 km sun-synchronous orbit; the enhanced Zhuque-2E variant, flying since November 2024, raises this to 6,000 kg LEO and 4,000 kg SSO. Per the cited page's infobox, the family has flown 8 times with 5 successes, and the baseline Zhuque-2 variant is now retired in favor of Zhuque-2E.",
